## 📄 README File 2 (Patch/Fix README)

```markdown
# Banner Component Fix Notes

## 🔧 Purpose
This README is meant to **correct or update** the main README file.  
Use this file when you need to fix mistakes or clarify instructions.

---

## ✅ Corrections
1. **Gradient Syntax**
   - In the main README, ensure you use `bg-gradient-to-r` (not `bg-linear-to-r`).

2. **Background Image Path**
   - If using imported images in React, apply them via:
     ```jsx
     style={{ backgroundImage: `url(${background})` }}
     ```
   - If using public assets, reference them like:
     ```jsx
     bg-[url('/assets/bg-shadow.png')]
     ```

3. **Container Class**
   - `container mx-auto` may add unwanted padding.  
     Use `w-full` if you want full-width banners.

---

## 🖼️ Corrected Example
```jsx
<div
  className="relative min-h-[60vh] w-full bg-cover bg-center"
  style={{ backgroundImage: `url(${background})` }}
>
  <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-500 to-indigo-300 opacity-70"></div>
  <div className="relative z-10 flex items-center justify-center h-full">
    <h1 className="text-white text-4xl font-bold">Banner</h1>
  </div>
</div>
## 🚀 Features
- **Background Image Support**: Uses imported assets or public paths.
- **Gradient Overlay**: Smooth gradient applied on top of the image.
- **Responsive Layout**: Works across different screen sizes.
- **Customizable Content**: Easily replace text or add buttons.

